1. Get an application of your choice, and push the code on GitHub.

2. Containerize the application.

3. Set up the secure infrastructure for the app on AWS using Terraform, and host the app on that infrastructure. Create a separate repo for Terraform Code on GitHub.

4. Create a CI/CD pipeline for the app. (Don't use the tools you already know)

5. It should build and deploy the code on push.

6. Changes should be visible on the public URL.

7. Set up basic monitoring and logging for the deployed application.

8. Document the assignment and share your learning.
